<hl>
<seg id=1> The supervisory project of China's insurance started in Beijing. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, 21 January In order to help the Chinese People's Bank supervise insurance regulations formulated by Chinese Insurance Organization of Foreign Capital, and to probe the standardization of insurance system and measures, a research project started in Beijing. </seg>
<seg id=3> English Royal Sun Union Insurance Groups and American Lincoln National Groups subsidized the project.  American Yon Dao Accountant Institute specifically undertook the project, and the total fund was US$1,400,000. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The supervisory project would do a systematic analysis on China's foreign capital insurance and its regulations. Using the experience of other countries for reference, they would pass a constructive research plan to support and perfect the development of China's insurance system. </seg>
<seg id=5> Based on the current supervisory insurance regulations of foreign capital by the Chinese People's Bank, the project would carry out further study to enhance the organization's operation administration, especially to develop early stage warning system. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It's reported that the new supervisory regulation would perfect insurance organization of foreign capital in the supervisory system of Chinese market, and help the Chinese People's Bank strengthen the whole supervisory system of insurance market. </seg>
</p>
